CIPHER.180.cipherString: With words at your disposal, you can see more clearly. Finding the words is another step in learning to see.
CIPHER.180.question: Solve this quote by Robin Kimmerer that has been encoded using the Aristocrat Cipher. What does it say?
CIPHER.180.author: Robin Kimmerer

CIPHER.181.question: Decrypt the following cipher text that has been encoded using the Cryptarithm Cipher. What do the values 76761 7892435 142340 decode to?

CIPHER.183.cipherString: What I do profess to know is that my lack of knowledge becomes clearer the more knowledgeable that I become.
CIPHER.183.question: Solve this quote by Craig D. Lounsbrough that has been encoded using the Aristocrat Cipher using a K1 alphabet. You are told it starts with WHAT. What does it say?
CIPHER.183.author: Craig D. Lounsbrough

CIPHER.185.cipherString: Nothing requires the architect's care more than the due proportions of buildings.
CIPHER.185.question: Solve this quote by Marcus V. Pollio that has been encoded using the Complete Columnar Cipher. You are told that the quote has PROPORT somewhere in it. What does it say?
CIPHER.185.author: Marcus V. Pollio

CIPHER.201.cipherString: Enfrenta los obstáculos a medida que se presenten, no pierdas energía temiendo lo que pueda haber en el futuro
CIPHER.201.question: Solve this quote by Isabel Allende in Spanish that has been encoded using the Xenocrypt Cipher using a K1 alphabet. What does it say?
CIPHER.201.author: Isabel Allende
CIPHER.201.translation: Face obstacles as they arise, don't waste energy fearing what may lie ahead.

CIPHER.192.cipherString: Love your life. Because your life is what you have to give.
CIPHER.192.question: You came across the following written on a wall in a cave. You notice that it's a quote by Tom Hiddleston encoded as a Baconian Cipher. What does it say?

CIPHER.188.cipherString: It is better to remain silent at the risk of being thought a fool, than to speak and remove all doubt.

CIPHER.188.author: Abigail Van Buren

CIPHER.195.cipherString: I do believe that if you haven't learnt about sadness, you cannot appreciate happiness.

CIPHER.196.cipherString: Its only when we can work with something that brings out our strengths that were of any real use.

CIPHER.196.author: Henning Mankell

CIPHER.197.cipherString: What is now proved was once only imagined.
CIPHER.197.question: Upon searching a room, the following were found on scraps of paper. You realize it's a quote by William Blake encoded as a Baconian Cipher. You are told that the cipher text DANCE HE DID GREAT SHOWS AN EGG BREAK decodes to be SONCEO. What does it say?
CIPHER.197.author: William Blake

CIPHER.205.cipherString: Do not read, as children do, to amuse yourself, or like the ambitious, for the purpose of instruction. No, read in order to live.
CIPHER.205.question: Gustave Flaubert offers an observation that has been encoded as a Patristocrat using a K2 alphabet. You are told it starts with DO NOT.  What does it say?
CIPHER.205.author: Gustave Flaubert

CIPHER.206.cipherString: In science read the newest works; in literature, the oldest.
CIPHER.206.question: A quote by Bulwer Lytton has been encoded using the Baconian Cipher for you to decode. What does it say?
CIPHER.206.author: Bulwer Lytton

CIPHER.203.cipherString: 'Tis the last rose of summer, Left blooming alone, All her lovely companions, Are faded and gone.
CIPHER.203.question: Thomas More offers an observation that has been encoded as an Aristocrat using a K1 alphabet. What does it say?
CIPHER.203.author: Thomas More

CIPHER.182.cipherString: Without craftsmanship, inspiration is a mere reed shaken in the wind.
CIPHER.182.question: Johannes Brahms was often heard to say the following phrase which has been encoded as a Porta Cipher using a keyword of ANGLES. What does it say?
CIPHER.182.author: Johannes Brahms

CIPHER.193.cipherString: The object of education is to prepare the young to educate themselves throughout their lives.
CIPHER.193.question: The following quote by Robert M. Hutchins needs to be decoded with the Aristocrat Cipher using a K2 alphabet.  The quote starts with THE.  What does it say?

CIPHER.200.cipherString: Sometimes you have to move backward to get a step forward.
CIPHER.200.question: A famous phrase by Amar Gopal Bose has been encoded as a Fractionated Morse Cipher. You are told that the quote has EPFORWARD in it corresponding to the encoded text Q H S I Y K T P L L F C, meaning C = –●●; F = –●×; H = ●––; I = ●●–; K = ––×; L = –×●; P = ×●–; Q = ×●×; S = ●××; T = ●–●; Y = ●×–. What does it say?

CIPHER.186.cipherString: All that mankind has done, thought, gained, or been, it is all lying in magic preservation in the pages of books.

CIPHER.186.author: Thomas Carlyle

CIPHER.189.cipherString: Originality is the fine art of remembering what you hear but forgetting where you heard it.
CIPHER.189.question: Someone passed you a piece of paper with this Nihilist Substitution Cipher encoded quote by Laurence J. Peter. They whispered to you that the length of the keyword is 6 and the 13th through 23rd cipher units (24 58 55 27 45 45 54 59 33 28 27) decode to be STHEFINEART. What does it say?

CIPHER.190.cipherString: Don't make friends who are comfortable to be with. Make friends who will force you to lever yourself up.
CIPHER.190.question: Thomas J. Watson offers us some advice that has been encoded as an Aristocrat using a K1 alphabet. What does it say?
CIPHER.190.author: Thomas J. Watson

CIPHER.194.cipherString: Failures fuel my drive to discovery.

CIPHER.204.cipherString: It takes a long time to become young.

CIPHER.184.cipherString: What's black and white and red all over? Santa covered with chimney soot.

CIPHER.187.cipherString: Life beats down and crushes the soul and art reminds you that you have one.
